function count_model_rows(df::DataFrame)
    return groupby(df, :model) |> collect |> x -> mapreduce(x -> length(x), +, init = 0)
end
```

This function uses the `groupby` function to group the data by the `model` column, then it collects the grouped data into a list of vectors. Finally, it applies the `mapreduce` function to sum up the number of rows for each model. The initial value of 0 is used to initialize the accumulation in `mapreduce`.
